Goal
The BT Global Australia – GMA integration aims to leverage Fiserv's GMA platform/Carat to reduce our dependency on third-party banks and processors in the Australian region, specifically focusing on Visa and MasterCard transactions.
This integration involves transitioning our merchants from their current NAB integration to Fiserv, where Fiserv will act as both the acquirer and the processor. This integration would leverage the Snowflake architecture framework created in the US via EPP.
With the new system, Arbiter will receive information about Visa and MasterCard disputes for Australian merchants directly from Fiserv. We will also be managing the submission of dispute representments directly to Fiserv.

Technical Assumptions
•	We assume that the relevant Chargebacks and Retrievals columns will be the same as those in the EPP schema within Snowflake.
•	Chargebacks and Retrievals are expected to follow the same dispute lifecycle as EPP, with the processor records being in the same shape and order as EPP, ensuring that the sequence of strategies applied remains consistent.
•	The evidence representment process is assumed to be the same as in EPP, involving submitting a zip file containing the evidence and an index file with the correct e-response version to the Fiserv SFTP, followed by the receipt of an acknowledgment file for the submitted batch.

LLD
Snowflake File Ingest
The Snowflake Ingest component would extract data from the Snowflake database and copy it into a file on the Amazon S3 bucket. This process is automated through a Snowflake task that triggers a stored procedure daily. The procedure is responsible for copying the files from the Snowflake database to Arbiter's S3 bucket.

Details
Snowflake Task: Runs once every day and executes the Snowflake stored procedure. Required for both Chargebacks and Retrievals.
Snowflake Stored Procedure: Contains the SQL query that extracts necessary data from Snowflake tables and exports to S3. Required for both Chargebacks and Retrievals.
Snowflake Permissions: Task and procedure grants with necessary permissions for creating and executing tasks and stored procedures. Stage to enable data unloading between Snowflake and S3.
Amazon S3 Bucket Configuration: Policies that allow Snowflake users to copy data into S3.

