Handling/Processing Processor Records
The HandleProcessorRecordService is the core component of Arbiter responsible for processing processor records. It determines appropriate strategies for dispute creation and updates, notifies merchants, and sends money movement updates to Funding.

Two possible flows:

1. When no existing Gateway transaction is found: A preemptive transaction lookup request is sent. Once the lookup request completes, DisputesWorker consumes the message from the SQS queue. It then calls ArbiterDisputeMessageService to create the transaction information in Arbiter and invokes HandleProcessorRecordService to run the strategy engine.
•	This flow handles processor records associated with dispute creation.
•	In certain EPP cases, the win/lose record arrives first — we still go through the preemptive transaction lookup and dispute consumer flow but apply update strategies.

2. When an associated transaction already exists: HandleProcessorRecordService is called directly from RowProcessor without a transaction lookup. The strategy engine is executed on the processor record.
•	This flow is associated with records related to updates to disputes.
•	A processor record could arrive and go through the Noop strategy during this flow.

