OPTION 3: Multiple Transaction Finder Classes + Multiple Transaction Details Tables with Region Column
✓ Pros	✗ Cons
Easy to implement with simple logic.	Need to maintain multiple classes with almost the same implementation and tables with similar data.

8. TransactionBuilder
Using the existing TransactionBuilder
If we have decided to add a region column to the TransactionDetails, the existing builder can be adapted.

Creating the new Fiserv TransactionBuilder
Makes use of TransactionFinder + TransactionDetails. The implementation is dependent on the chosen solution for transaction_finder and transaction_details.

Pseudocode:
module Fiserv
  class TransactionBuilder
    include TransactionBuilderCommon

    def build_if_missing(transaction_public_id = nil)
      # If using multiple transaction finders, use region to call the appropriate one.
      # If using single transaction finder, nothing changes here.
      existing_transaction = processor_record.transaction_finder.transaction
      transaction_public_id = existing_transaction.public_id if existing_transaction.present?

      super(transaction_public_id)
    end

    # If using multiple transaction details, create class name using region:
    # details_class = "TransactionDetails#{region}".constantize
    # details_class.new(...)
    # If using single transaction details, just pass region along with current details.
    def transaction_details
      TransactionDetails.new(
        processor_merchant_id: processor_record.processor_merchant_id,
        processor_transaction_identifier: processor_record.processor_transaction_identifier,
        region: processor_record.region
      )
    end
  end
end

